China should tighten imports of ordinarygoods and restrict or even forbid import of goods which can bemade domestically, Premier Zhao Ziyang said.    He told the National People's Congress, China's parliament,that the country's foreign exchange is limited and must be usedwhere it is most needed. "We should expand production of importsubstitutes and increase their proportion," he said. On exports,China should increase its proportion of manufactured goods,especially textiles, light industrial goods, electronics andmachinery, he said.    Zhao said China should lower the cost of exports andcontrol the export of goods that incur too much loss.    Zhao said China should work to provide a more favourableinvestment environment for foreign businessmen. Reuter&#3;